"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-olympics-news-2024-olympic-basketball-roster-usa-paris-lebron-durant-curry\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"LeBron James, Kevin Durant, Stephen Curry and Joel Embiid headline arguably the most star-studded Olympic men's basketball roster since the 1990s as the U.S. eyes a fifth consecutive title in Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 198, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 12, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LeBron James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}, {\"begin\": 20, \"end\": 26, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.608680540680897e-29, \"text\": \"Durant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\"}, {\"begin\": 28, \"end\": 41, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2597312857626252e-50, \"text\": \"Stephen Curry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\"}, {\"begin\": 46, \"end\": 57, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joel_Embiid\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Joel Embiid\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joel_Embiid\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joel_Embiid\"}, {\"begin\": 192, \"end\": 197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999729448067, \"rank\": 2.7055118895668928e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 12-player team was announced Wednesday, 100 days out from the July 26 Opening Ceremony.\", \"from\": 200, \"to\": 291, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The group includes, for the first time on an Olympic roster, four players who previously won an NBA MVP (James, Durant, Curry and Embiid), plus 11 2024 NBA All-Stars and the most combined prior All-Star selections (84) of any Olympic team.\", \"from\": 293, \"to\": 532, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 389, \"end\": 396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1222096649935036e-22, \"text\": \"NBA MVP\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\"}, {\"begin\": 398, \"end\": 403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2443262953221964e-23, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}, {\"begin\": 445, \"end\": 448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8747278051824842e-31, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It will not be easy.\", \"from\": 534, \"to\": 555, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We have great respect for all the other teams, but, certainly, this is going to be an iconic roster,\\\" USA Basketball managing director Grant Hill said on TODAY.\", \"from\": 556, \"to\": 716, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 658, \"end\": 672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Basketball\", \"score\": 0.9999320313684995, \"rank\": 6.797325164888751e-05, \"text\": \"USA Basketball\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Basketball\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Basketball\"}, {\"begin\": 691, \"end\": 701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Hill\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1255310096559353e-31, \"text\": \"Grant Hill\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Hill\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grant_Hill\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"2024 U.S. Olympic Men's Basketball Roster  The seven returning Olympians are the most for any U.S. men's team in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 718, \"to\": 847, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 812, \"end\": 816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999800588741, \"rank\": 1.993848713562095e-08, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Every player on the team previously made an NBA All-Star team for the second time in Olympic history after 1996.\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 960, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 892, \"end\": 904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_All-Star_Game\", \"score\": 0.9999999999308784, \"rank\": 6.89105994068069e-11, \"text\": \"NBA All-Star\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_All-Star_Game\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_All-Star_Game\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The original Dream Team for the 1992 Barcelona Games - the first to include NBA players - had three previous MVPs - Larry Bird, Magic Johnson and Michael Jordan - and a combined 68 All-Star selections at the time, one fewer than the 1996 team.\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 1205, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1038, \"end\": 1041, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8747278051824842e-31, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 1078, \"end\": 1088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Bird\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Larry Bird\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Bird\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Bird\"}, {\"begin\": 1090, \"end\": 1103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magic_Johnson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.879587998463874e-28, \"text\": \"Magic Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magic_Johnson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magic_Johnson\"}, {\"begin\": 1108, \"end\": 1122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Jordan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.969653077972898e-42, \"text\": \"Michael Jordan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Jordan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Jordan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the start of the Barcelona Games, Bird, Johnson and Jordan owned a combined 10 NBA titles.\", \"from\": 1207, \"to\": 1300, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1250, \"end\": 1257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magic_Johnson\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.259506355633933e-13, \"text\": \"Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magic_Johnson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magic_Johnson\"}, {\"begin\": 1262, \"end\": 1268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Jordan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.940615105712847e-23, \"text\": \"Jordan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Jordan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Jordan\"}, {\"begin\": 1289, \"end\": 1292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8747278051824842e-31, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Currently, James, Durant and Curry own a combined 10 NBA titles.\", \"from\": 1301, \"to\": 1365, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1312, \"end\": 1317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2443262953221964e-23, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}, {\"begin\": 1354, \"end\": 1357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8747278051824842e-31, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The record for oldest U.S. Olympic men's basketball player - held by Bird, who was 35 years, 7 months in 1992 - will be broken by James (39), Curry (36) and Durant (35 years, 10 months).\", \"from\": 1367, \"to\": 1553, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1497, \"end\": 1502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2443262953221964e-23, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}, {\"begin\": 1524, \"end\": 1530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.608680540680897e-29, \"text\": \"Durant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Overall, this is the oldest U.S. Olympic men's basketball roster in history with an average of 30 years, 9 months old when the Games open.\", \"from\": 1555, \"to\": 1693, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The previous oldest team - 1996 - averaged 29 years, 10 months old.\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1761, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"James returns after playing on gold-medal teams in 2008 and 2012 and a bronze-medal team in 2004.\", \"from\": 1763, \"to\": 1860, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1763, \"end\": 1768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2443262953221964e-23, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This summer, James, Diana Taurasi and Spain's Rudy Fernandez can become the first basketball players to have Olympic careers span 20 years, according to the OlyMADMen.\", \"from\": 1861, \"to\": 2028, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1874, \"end\": 1879, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2443262953221964e-23, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}, {\"begin\": 1881, \"end\": 1894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diana_Taurasi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Diana Taurasi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diana_Taurasi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diana_Taurasi\"}, {\"begin\": 1899, \"end\": 1904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999608794504, \"rank\": 3.7926601342289145e-08, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1907, \"end\": 1921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rudy_Fernandez_(actor)\", \"score\": 0.586613408960599, \"rank\": 0.6972789115645815, \"text\": \"Rudy Fernandez\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rudy_Fernandez_(actor)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rudy_Fernandez_(actor)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Durant led the U.S. in points per game at the last three Olympics, and in Tokyo broke Carmelo Anthony's career Olympic points record for an American man.\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2183, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2104, \"end\": 2109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.7335851077801994, \"rank\": 0.36316278536867397, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 2116, \"end\": 2131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carmelo_Anthony\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carmelo Anthony\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carmelo_Anthony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carmelo_Anthony\"}, {\"begin\": 2170, \"end\": 2178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_League\", \"score\": 0.9998385163367051, \"rank\": 0.00014203445891616774, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6631808\", \"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Durant is up to 435 points, which is 53 points shy of Lisa Leslie's U.S. Olympic points record for women or men.\", \"from\": 2184, \"to\": 2296, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2238, \"end\": 2249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Leslie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lisa Leslie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Leslie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Leslie\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He can also break his tie with Anthony for the most Olympic men's basketball gold medals.\", \"from\": 2298, \"to\": 2387, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Curry goes to his first Olympics, though he was on gold-medal FIBA World Cup teams in 2010 and 2014.\", \"from\": 2389, \"to\": 2489, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. head coach is his head coach with the Warriors - Steve Kerr.\", \"from\": 2490, \"to\": 2559, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Embiid had three options for international basketball and chose the U.S. over France and Cameroon.\", \"from\": 2561, \"to\": 2659, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2639, \"end\": 2645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9996408211274588, \"rank\": 0.00035930666253511135, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2650, \"end\": 2658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cameroon_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9986543895718707, \"rank\": 0.001347423532088887, \"text\": \"Cameroon\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cameroon_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cameroon_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He will play in his first major international tournament.\", \"from\": 2660, \"to\": 2717, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Leonard, a two-time NBA Finals MVP and two-time Defensive Player of the Year, is also making his senior international debut.\", \"from\": 2719, \"to\": 2843, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2739, \"end\": 2753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Finals_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBA Finals MVP\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Finals_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Finals_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\"}, {\"begin\": 2739, \"end\": 2753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Finals_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBA Finals MVP\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Finals_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Finals_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2012, he was on the U.S. select team of young players who practiced with the Olympic team after his rookie season.\", \"from\": 2844, \"to\": 2961, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Defense was certainly a priority, having guys that are capable of locking down, of guarding multiple sets within a possession,\\\" Hill said.\", \"from\": 2963, \"to\": 3102, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think a maturity, an emotional maturity, and then just blending personalities.\", \"from\": 3103, \"to\": 3184, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sometimes you can have a collection of the best, but it's most important to have the best fit.\\\"\", \"from\": 3185, \"to\": 3280, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tatum, Booker, Adebayo and Holiday were all on the Tokyo Olympic team.\", \"from\": 3282, \"to\": 3352, \"entities\": [{\"begi